00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:06,860 --> 00:00:09,795
(Love has no age...)

2
00:00:09,796 --> 00:00:15,202
(because it is constantly reborn.)

3
00:00:15,802 --> 00:00:17,002
Butterflies?

4
00:00:17,651 --> 00:00:19,885
I haven't felt butterflies in a long time.

5
00:00:20,174 --> 00:00:21,108
What should I do?

6
00:00:22,266 --> 00:00:23,299
Romance?

7
00:00:24,201 --> 00:00:26,147
I guess I've been putting work
before romance.

8
00:00:26,736 --> 00:00:29,538
Being alone became comfortable.

9
00:00:30,774 --> 00:00:32,753
But now,
I can't keep putting it off anymore.

10
00:00:34,011 --> 00:00:36,579
I want to feel butterflies again,

11
00:00:36,580 --> 00:00:38,881
like I did in my 20s.

12
00:00:39,817 --> 00:00:40,995
I want to fall in love.

13
00:00:42,619 --> 00:00:45,132
Because I want a love
that gives me a dopamine rush.

14
00:00:46,156 --> 00:00:49,859
I honestly don't think younger men
would turn me down.

15
00:00:50,794 --> 00:00:52,494
I bought a house...

16
00:00:52,495 --> 00:00:54,363
in one of the best neighborhoods
in the country.

17
00:00:55,021 --> 00:00:56,808
He could just stay home
and be a house husband.

18
00:00:56,833 --> 00:00:58,012
I can bring home the bacon.

19
00:00:58,269 --> 00:00:59,813
I look much younger than my age,

20
00:00:59,903 --> 00:01:01,670
and I'm very capable.

21
00:01:02,305 --> 00:01:05,139
What worries me is
whether I'll actually find...

22
00:01:05,140 --> 00:01:06,554
someone I'm attracted to.

23
00:01:06,635 --> 00:01:08,915
Will I really be able to feel attracted
to a younger man?

24
00:01:10,180 --> 00:01:11,680
I'll make them fall for me.

25
00:01:12,115 --> 00:01:13,527
With just a few glances...

26
00:01:13,884 --> 00:01:15,251
and a little playful banter,

27
00:01:15,719 --> 00:01:16,964
they always fall for me.

28
00:01:17,854 --> 00:01:20,000
Younger men tend to be
very straightforward.

29
00:01:21,058 --> 00:01:22,236
Can't you just stay?

30
00:01:23,226 --> 00:01:24,405
Should we spend the night here?

31
00:01:25,195 --> 00:01:26,640
Do you think you can handle this?

32
00:01:27,931 --> 00:01:30,199
If you're okay with it,

33
00:01:30,934 --> 00:01:32,580
I want us to be together
even after filming ends.

34
00:01:33,603 --> 00:01:36,104
But what would we actually do
in real life?

35
00:01:36,105 --> 00:01:37,072
A romance?

36
00:01:37,073 --> 00:01:40,375
From my perspective,
there's no attraction.

37
00:01:40,577 --> 00:01:44,413
I don't understand
why you won't even try to see me as a man.

38
00:01:45,415 --> 00:01:47,361
You really are young, aren't you?

39
00:01:48,318 --> 00:01:51,186
This is the first time I've ever wished...

40
00:01:51,421 --> 00:01:52,287
I were older.

41
00:01:52,589 --> 00:01:54,056
What's wrong with a 12-year age gap?

42
00:01:54,057 --> 00:01:55,157
Could this actually work?

43
00:01:55,158 --> 00:01:57,026
I have a career too, you know.

44
00:01:57,928 --> 00:02:00,941
Will I really be able to maintain
this relationship after the show ends?

45
00:02:01,064 --> 00:02:02,476
You and I just don't work.

46
00:02:02,832 --> 00:02:04,366
It's driving me crazy.

47
00:02:05,269 --> 00:02:08,370
I came here to find someone I could marry.

48
00:02:08,738 --> 00:02:11,907
(Mind the Noona Gap 2)

49
00:02:15,445 --> 00:02:17,579
Hold on. What is happening?

50
00:02:18,315 --> 00:02:20,004
This is way bolder than I expected.

51
00:02:20,029 --> 00:02:20,929
It really is bold.

52
00:02:21,217 --> 00:02:25,954
And this is only the prologue.
Even so, this season feels different.

53
00:02:25,955 --> 00:02:27,723
- It's incredibly intense.
- Right.

54
00:02:27,724 --> 00:02:28,690
Is it really that different?

55
00:02:28,691 --> 00:02:31,927
If Season One felt like a calm lake,

56
00:02:31,928 --> 00:02:35,163
this season feels
like a stormy ocean in Bali.

57
00:02:36,066 --> 00:02:37,700
Wait. We should point out something.

58
00:02:37,701 --> 00:02:40,169
Someone is sitting next to me
who wasn't here last season.

59
00:02:40,170 --> 00:02:41,548
Could you introduce yourself?

60
00:02:42,038 --> 00:02:44,339
Hello, I'm DinDin, the ideal younger guy.

61
00:02:46,042 --> 00:02:47,009
I can give you that.

62
00:02:47,077 --> 00:02:50,546
Honestly,
I think I got cast on this show...

63
00:02:50,547 --> 00:02:52,515
because older women...

64
00:02:53,350 --> 00:02:54,750
have always loved me.

65
00:02:55,585 --> 00:02:58,020
A lot of them used to say,

66
00:02:58,021 --> 00:03:00,355
"You're going to become irresistible..."

67
00:03:00,557 --> 00:03:02,925
"once you hit your mid-30s."

68
00:03:03,293 --> 00:03:05,461
And back then,
they always said I was too young.

69
00:03:05,462 --> 00:03:07,062
- The older women said that?
- How old are you now?

70
00:03:07,063 --> 00:03:08,530
I'm 36.

71
00:03:08,765 --> 00:03:09,698
That's Korean age.

72
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:13,411
- So you're in your mid-30s now.
- Exactly. The irresistible age.

73
00:03:13,436 --> 00:03:15,637
I've aged like fine wine.

74
00:03:15,638 --> 00:03:18,407
When Season One aired,

75
00:03:18,408 --> 00:03:21,076
the biggest issue
everyone talked about was...

76
00:03:21,077 --> 00:03:24,880
the age gap between the older women
and the younger men.

77
00:03:25,482 --> 00:03:27,483
People were obsessed
with the biggest age difference.

78
00:03:27,484 --> 00:03:28,985
And the biggest gap was 13 years.

79
00:03:28,986 --> 00:03:30,387
- That's...
- The biggest gap was.

80
00:03:30,388 --> 00:03:31,720
That's huge.

81
00:03:31,721 --> 00:03:32,855
- You mean, 13?
- That's a really big gap.

82
00:03:32,856 --> 00:03:35,357
How much older were your exes?

83
00:03:35,358 --> 00:03:39,495
Back when I was in my mid-20s,

84
00:03:39,829 --> 00:03:41,930
I dated someone five years older than me.

85
00:03:42,298 --> 00:03:43,477
She was already in her 30s.

86
00:03:43,671 --> 00:03:45,768
So a guy in his 20s
dating a woman in her 30s.

87
00:03:45,769 --> 00:03:46,769
That couldn't have been easy.

88
00:03:46,770 --> 00:03:50,239
At first, the fact
that she was older made me...

89
00:03:50,573 --> 00:03:51,941
really excited.

90
00:03:52,375 --> 00:03:54,788
She used to drive me home in her car.

91
00:03:55,578 --> 00:03:57,691
Just that alone gave me a dopamine rush.

92
00:03:58,382 --> 00:04:00,415
One time while we were driving
on Gangbyeonbuk-ro, I literally screamed.

93
00:04:00,416 --> 00:04:02,084
- I was so excited.
- That's adorable.

94
00:04:02,085 --> 00:04:03,018
- You screamed next to her?
- I was like, "Yay!"

95
00:04:03,019 --> 00:04:03,919
"Yay!"

96
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:05,153
- "She's driving me home!"
- That's cute.

97
00:04:05,154 --> 00:04:07,355
"She's the first girlfriend
who's ever driven me home!"

98
00:04:07,356 --> 00:04:08,736
That's how I was in the beginning.

99
00:04:08,858 --> 00:04:10,525
But after some time had passed,

100
00:04:10,894 --> 00:04:12,771
I realized we were just two people
in a relationship.

101
00:04:12,796 --> 00:04:14,842
There are certain thrills
only older women can give you.

102
00:04:16,099 --> 00:04:18,233
I see. So in a long-term relationship,

103
00:04:18,234 --> 00:04:20,836
age doesn't really become a huge issue?

104
00:04:20,837 --> 00:04:22,071
At the end of the day,
it's just a man and a woman.

105
00:04:22,072 --> 00:04:23,439
Exactly. It's still just a relationship.

106
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:25,208
Regardless of age,
a relationship is still a relationship.

107
00:04:25,209 --> 00:04:27,309
Emotionally, it's all the same.

108
00:04:27,744 --> 00:04:29,356
- In the end, yes.
- But, you see...

109
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:31,480
the beginning is usually
the difficult part.

110
00:04:32,182 --> 00:04:35,985
Older women tend to overthink
whether the relationship can really work.

111
00:04:36,225 --> 00:04:38,265
But younger men just believe it will.

112
00:04:38,521 --> 00:04:40,589
That's really how men think?

113
00:04:40,590 --> 00:04:41,590
- Yes.
- The younger men?

114
00:04:41,615 --> 00:04:43,103
Because we're men, after all.

115
00:04:43,893 --> 00:04:45,527
They just believe it'll work anyway.

116
00:04:45,728 --> 00:04:48,596
The women try to stay cautious,
but once they open up,

117
00:04:48,597 --> 00:04:49,597
they fall hard.

118
00:04:49,732 --> 00:04:50,732
(That's so romantic.)

119
00:04:50,733 --> 00:04:51,966
Older women really fall hard?

120
00:04:51,967 --> 00:04:53,835
Yes. They really do.

121
00:04:54,037 --> 00:04:54,870
That sounds fun.

122
00:04:54,871 --> 00:04:57,506
(What kind of drama will unfold
this season?)

123
00:04:58,608 --> 00:05:00,776
(A spring day in April)

124
00:05:00,777 --> 00:05:01,843
The weather is perfect.

125
00:05:01,844 --> 00:05:04,379
If you meet the right person in April,
you're getting married before you know it.

126
00:05:04,380 --> 00:05:05,480
- Right.
- Seriously.

127
00:05:05,481 --> 00:05:07,115
- You just get swept away.
- Totally enchanted.

128
00:05:07,317 --> 00:05:13,822
(The second Yeon House
for older women and younger men)

129
00:05:13,823 --> 00:05:15,591
"Yeon House." It's been a while.

130
00:05:20,296 --> 00:05:25,634
(Who will be the first to arrive
at Yeon House?)

131
00:05:30,173 --> 00:05:32,252
She's here. The first older woman.

132
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:39,226
Just looking at her makes me excited.

133
00:05:40,583 --> 00:05:42,717
She seems so elegant.

134
00:05:44,888 --> 00:05:48,057
(Koo Ji Seung)

135
00:05:48,058 --> 00:05:50,471
She totally looks like the type
younger men would love.

136
00:05:51,127 --> 00:05:54,062
Whenever people ask me
what I love most in life,

137
00:05:54,063 --> 00:05:56,798
I answer that it's the sense
of achievement I get from work.

138
00:05:57,534 --> 00:05:59,101
I think work has always come
before romance.

139
00:05:59,102 --> 00:06:00,202
Right.

140
00:06:00,403 --> 00:06:03,338
I probably had opportunities
to get married before,

141
00:06:03,773 --> 00:06:05,040
but I was never completely sure.

142
00:06:05,041 --> 00:06:07,976
(She had opportunities but wasn't sure.)

143
00:06:08,444 --> 00:06:10,078
But I've changed a lot now.

144
00:06:10,380 --> 00:06:13,460
Now I want to experience romance
without overthinking everything.

145
00:06:14,884 --> 00:06:16,985
It seems like she's finally made room
in her life for romance.

146
00:06:16,986 --> 00:06:18,832
- Now that her career is more settled.
- Exactly.

147
00:06:20,523 --> 00:06:23,904
I want to find someone
who can truly put each other first.

148
00:06:35,023 --> 00:06:36,290
Where should I sit?

149
00:06:39,075 --> 00:06:44,846
(The communal living room is still empty.)

150
00:06:50,386 --> 00:06:51,920
She looks so young.

151
00:06:51,921 --> 00:06:53,421
She really does.

152
00:06:54,891 --> 00:06:56,904
The sunlight is way too strong over here.

153
00:06:59,395 --> 00:07:01,162
(Blazing)

154
00:07:14,220 --> 00:07:17,556
(While Ji Seung adjusts
to life at Yeon House,)

155
00:07:17,581 --> 00:07:19,326
How is she feeling right now?

156
00:07:23,486 --> 00:07:28,390
(a car arrives at Yeon House.)

157
00:07:29,292 --> 00:07:32,394
(Is this the second older woman?)

158
00:07:32,395 --> 00:07:33,428
(Or the first younger man?)

159
00:07:33,429 --> 00:07:34,796
I think it's a man.

160
00:07:34,999 --> 00:07:37,077
You can tell by the way he drives.

161
00:07:41,971 --> 00:07:43,250
Was the driver a woman?

162
00:07:45,942 --> 00:07:48,477
Her walk feels completely different
from Ji Seung's.

163
00:07:48,478 --> 00:07:50,223
She seems confident.

164
00:07:52,849 --> 00:07:54,049
(Park Ji Hye)

165
00:07:54,050 --> 00:07:56,452
She looks like someone
who takes very good care of herself.

166
00:07:56,719 --> 00:07:59,066
Younger men tend to be proactive.

167
00:07:59,389 --> 00:08:01,535
I want a romance
that's bold and provocative.

168
00:08:01,650 --> 00:08:04,164
I think I came here looking
for that kind of adrenaline rush.

169
00:08:05,161 --> 00:08:10,031
Whenever I personally think
someone looks attractive,

170
00:08:10,066 --> 00:08:11,612
they always end up falling for me.

171
00:08:11,968 --> 00:08:13,246
So the guys...

172
00:08:13,436 --> 00:08:15,237
should be nervous. I'm serious.

173
00:08:15,638 --> 00:08:17,551
I'll never let my guard down.

174
00:08:18,008 --> 00:08:18,874
Never.

175
00:08:19,409 --> 00:08:22,144
Her charm is completely different
from Ji Seung's.

176
00:08:22,169 --> 00:08:25,471
Younger men go crazy...

177
00:08:25,682 --> 00:08:26,827
for women like her.

178
00:08:28,284 --> 00:08:29,351
(Grinning)

179
00:08:29,352 --> 00:08:30,731
I love her confidence.

180
00:08:37,427 --> 00:08:39,128
- Hello.
- Hi.

181
00:08:40,063 --> 00:08:41,764
- Hello.
- Hi.

182
00:08:43,466 --> 00:08:44,733
Nice to meet you.

183
00:08:44,935 --> 00:08:47,502
Hello, it's nice to meet you.

184
00:08:47,503 --> 00:08:48,636
(The older women meet for the first time.)

185
00:08:49,739 --> 00:08:50,539
They're so different.

186
00:08:50,540 --> 00:08:52,708
- Totally different characters.
- They are.

187
00:08:54,911 --> 00:08:56,745
Because the sunlight was so strong
over there,

188
00:08:56,746 --> 00:08:58,647
- I moved here instead.
- Really?

189
00:08:58,648 --> 00:08:59,481
Yes.

190
00:09:00,116 --> 00:09:02,250
You're very tall.

191
00:09:13,095 --> 00:09:13,895
(Glancing)

192
00:09:14,597 --> 00:09:15,597
(Peeking)

193
00:09:16,275 --> 00:09:17,542
They're checking each other out
already, right?

194
00:09:17,567 --> 00:09:18,500
Definitely.

195
00:09:18,501 --> 00:09:20,335
But they'll soon realize...

196
00:09:20,336 --> 00:09:21,837
they have completely different styles.

197
00:09:27,276 --> 00:09:28,455
Aren't you nervous?

198
00:09:28,611 --> 00:09:30,078
I am.

199
00:09:31,981 --> 00:09:35,450
About two weeks ago,
I wasn't nervous at all.

200
00:09:35,451 --> 00:09:37,230
- I thought it would just be fun.
- Right?

201
00:09:38,054 --> 00:09:40,967
But around five days ago,
I suddenly started getting really nervous.

202
00:09:41,858 --> 00:09:43,937
I haven't been able to sleep since then.

203
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,493
Same here.

204
00:09:46,396 --> 00:09:47,262
This is...

205
00:09:48,231 --> 00:09:49,698
way more nerve-racking than I expected.

206
00:09:49,699 --> 00:09:51,166
I've never been this nervous...

207
00:09:51,167 --> 00:09:53,035
- in my life.
- Seriously.

208
00:09:53,036 --> 00:09:54,536
This feels so different.

209
00:09:56,739 --> 00:09:57,872
(Turning around)

210
00:09:58,141 --> 00:09:59,386
Is someone coming?

211
00:09:59,675 --> 00:10:00,654
Do you see anyone?

212
00:10:02,562 --> 00:10:04,257
They're both nervous.

213
00:10:07,706 --> 00:10:08,706
Seems like a woman.

214
00:10:11,473 --> 00:10:14,609
(Choi Yu Jin)

215
00:10:14,610 --> 00:10:16,345
Everyone is so pretty.

216
00:10:18,861 --> 00:10:20,715
I'm usually easygoing.

217
00:10:21,101 --> 00:10:23,010
But when I'm with someone
I'm attracted to,

218
00:10:23,034 --> 00:10:24,719
I get super feminine.

219
00:10:25,647 --> 00:10:28,648
I came to find a guy
who brings out my feminine side.

220
00:10:29,645 --> 00:10:30,645
When it comes to love,

221
00:10:31,660 --> 00:10:35,030
chemistry matters more than age.

222
00:10:36,245 --> 00:10:40,371
I want a relationship
that gives me butterflies.

223
00:10:41,250 --> 00:10:44,172
If you're in your 30s, you can relate.

224
00:10:45,391 --> 00:10:48,078
- Hello.
- Hello.

225
00:10:48,897 --> 00:10:53,181
- Hello.
- Hello.

226
00:10:53,999 --> 00:10:56,958
- I'm so nervous.
- We were saying the same thing.

227
00:10:56,983 --> 00:10:58,611
I'm so nervous.

228
00:10:59,586 --> 00:11:01,256
She has a smiley face.

229
00:11:01,478 --> 00:11:05,305
- Right. We're all feeling the same way.
- We feel the same.

230
00:11:06,237 --> 00:11:09,637
(With Yu Jin joining them,)

231
00:11:09,662 --> 00:11:12,634
(now there are three older women.)

232
00:11:12,635 --> 00:11:13,635
I'm so nervous.

233
00:11:18,707 --> 00:11:20,209
(Staring)

234
00:11:23,571 --> 00:11:24,571
It'll be...

235
00:11:26,450 --> 00:11:27,707
a fun week, right?

236
00:11:30,565 --> 00:11:32,812
I think I'll be comfortable after today.

237
00:11:33,156 --> 00:11:34,247
Me too.

238
00:11:36,003 --> 00:11:38,785
I might not even want to go back home.

239
00:11:43,094 --> 00:11:44,094
Ji Hye...

240
00:11:45,180 --> 00:11:47,927
seems really charismatic.

241
00:11:48,148 --> 00:11:51,380
She seems straightforward.

242
00:11:52,259 --> 00:11:56,102
My first impression of Ji Seung was
that she seemed elegant.

243
00:12:03,505 --> 00:12:05,959
Just imagining being there is suffocating.

244
00:12:05,983 --> 00:12:06,822
I know.

245
00:12:06,823 --> 00:12:08,290
(Older women with different vibes
are getting to know each other.)

246
00:12:13,395 --> 00:12:17,532
(The fourth older woman is
arriving at Yeon House.)

247
00:12:25,021 --> 00:12:27,709
She has a different kind of beauty.

248
00:12:29,277 --> 00:12:31,293
(Yoo Ju Hee)

249
00:12:31,294 --> 00:12:33,406
The younger guys will lose their minds.

250
00:12:34,924 --> 00:12:37,510
I vibe better with younger guys.

251
00:12:39,365 --> 00:12:41,314
I can be more honest with them.

252
00:12:41,751 --> 00:12:44,459
I like that I can be myself around them
without holding back.

253
00:12:44,698 --> 00:12:45,918
That's their charm.

254
00:12:46,251 --> 00:12:49,318
I seem calm at first,
but when I get comfortable with someone,

255
00:12:49,391 --> 00:12:51,232
I become more fun.

256
00:12:51,327 --> 00:12:54,669
I think that twist is my charm.

257
00:12:55,873 --> 00:12:58,026
She goes horse riding?

258
00:12:58,379 --> 00:13:01,432
- What about it?
- That's amazing.

259
00:13:01,433 --> 00:13:03,121
What do you think about women
who go horse riding?

260
00:13:03,145 --> 00:13:04,548
