00:27:12,675 --> 00:27:14,342
For them, the moment I enter,

529
00:27:14,342 --> 00:27:16,575
- I can lie down and act like this.
- You're right.

530
00:27:18,542 --> 00:27:19,575
Did you introduce yourselves?

531
00:27:19,575 --> 00:27:21,909
No, we were going to once you got here.

532
00:27:21,909 --> 00:27:23,209
We were waiting for you.

533
00:27:24,063 --> 00:27:25,323
So, you were waiting.

534
00:27:25,709 --> 00:27:26,775
Do I go first?

535
00:27:27,075 --> 00:27:28,975
My name is Lee Yun So.

536
00:27:29,409 --> 00:27:31,175
- Yun So?
- Yun Sol?

537
00:27:31,175 --> 00:27:33,538
- It's Yun So.
- I've never heard of that name.

538
00:27:34,375 --> 00:27:35,409
Yun So.

539
00:27:35,975 --> 00:27:36,975
That's a nice name.

540
00:27:38,409 --> 00:27:40,775
My name is Yoo Ju Hee.

541
00:27:40,775 --> 00:27:42,375
- Ju Hee!
- Ju Hee.

542
00:27:42,375 --> 00:27:43,442
Yoo Ju Hee.

543
00:27:45,109 --> 00:27:46,475
Ju Hee.

544
00:27:47,242 --> 00:27:48,242
Yoo Ju Hee.

545
00:27:48,242 --> 00:27:49,709
I'm Lee Jun Han.

546
00:27:49,709 --> 00:27:50,942
- Ju Han?
- Jun Han.

547
00:27:50,942 --> 00:27:52,542
- Jun Han?
- Jun Han.

548
00:27:52,542 --> 00:27:54,809
Jun Han.

549
00:27:55,042 --> 00:27:56,509
- Jun Han.
- Jun Han.

550
00:27:56,509 --> 00:27:57,742
Jun Han.

551
00:27:58,209 --> 00:27:59,809
I'm Park Ji Hye.

552
00:27:59,809 --> 00:28:01,709
- Ji Hye.
- Park Ji Hye.

553
00:28:02,375 --> 00:28:04,109
- Ji Hye.
- Ji Hye.

554
00:28:04,975 --> 00:28:07,775
- I'm Koo Ji Seung.
- Ji Seung.

555
00:28:07,775 --> 00:28:09,242
That name suits you well.

556
00:28:09,242 --> 00:28:10,609
- You're right.
- Doesn't it?

557
00:28:11,009 --> 00:28:12,142
It's gender-neutral.

558
00:28:12,142 --> 00:28:13,142
(Shy)

559
00:28:13,209 --> 00:28:14,675
I'm Lee Si Won.

560
00:28:15,442 --> 00:28:16,509
Si Won.

561
00:28:18,409 --> 00:28:20,175
I'm Yoo Jin Woo.

562
00:28:20,175 --> 00:28:21,409
- Jin Woo?
- Jin Woo.

563
00:28:21,409 --> 00:28:23,109
My brother has the same name.

564
00:28:23,109 --> 00:28:24,209
It's an honor.

565
00:28:25,242 --> 00:28:26,442
- Yoo Jin Woo.
- Jin Woo.

566
00:28:27,609 --> 00:28:29,775
I'm Choi Yu Jin.

567
00:28:30,142 --> 00:28:31,175
Yu Jin.

568
00:28:31,942 --> 00:28:33,509
- Choi Yu Jin.
- Choi Yu Jin.

569
00:28:35,275 --> 00:28:36,409
- Choi Yu Jin.
- Choi Yu Jin.

570
00:28:38,409 --> 00:28:42,309
(The older women and younger men
only know each other's names.)

571
00:28:44,075 --> 00:28:46,942
So we're all eating here today?

572
00:28:46,942 --> 00:28:47,942
Are we cooking something?

573
00:28:47,942 --> 00:28:49,942
I think so.

574
00:28:51,409 --> 00:28:53,175
Is anyone good at cooking here?

575
00:28:53,175 --> 00:28:54,642
- Korean food.
- I can make Korean food.

576
00:28:56,309 --> 00:28:58,209
I can at least cook doenjang stew.

577
00:28:58,209 --> 00:28:59,509
- Really?
- Really?

578
00:29:00,709 --> 00:29:02,709
- I can grill meat.
- You can?

579
00:29:02,709 --> 00:29:03,709
Great.

580
00:29:03,775 --> 00:29:04,775
I can cook ramyeon.

581
00:29:05,342 --> 00:29:07,942
There. We're done.

582
00:29:08,675 --> 00:29:10,175
I can just stay still.

583
00:29:10,875 --> 00:29:11,875
Anything.

584
00:29:12,242 --> 00:29:13,242
I can make anything.

585
00:29:13,742 --> 00:29:14,975
- Anything?
- Yes.

586
00:29:14,975 --> 00:29:15,975
Even malatang.

587
00:29:16,375 --> 00:29:17,742
Malatang? Really?

588
00:29:19,275 --> 00:29:20,275
Really.

589
00:29:20,275 --> 00:29:23,409
But guys usually don't eat malatang.

590
00:29:23,409 --> 00:29:24,909
I can only eat mild ones.

591
00:29:26,042 --> 00:29:27,209
You can't eat spicy ones?

592
00:29:27,209 --> 00:29:28,209
I can.

593
00:29:28,209 --> 00:29:30,288
- But it hits me hard the next day.
- You feel sick?

594
00:29:32,342 --> 00:29:33,342
He's cute.

595
00:29:33,375 --> 00:29:36,809
Jin Woo is kind of a delicate guy.

596
00:29:36,809 --> 00:29:37,809
I see it.

597
00:29:37,809 --> 00:29:38,842
You want to take care of him.

598
00:29:39,442 --> 00:29:40,699
You seem like that type.

599
00:29:42,209 --> 00:29:44,375
- He looks like he can't eat spicy food.
- What does that mean?

600
00:29:44,375 --> 00:29:46,342
You look like you can't.

601
00:29:46,742 --> 00:29:49,241
You don't think of me
as a younger brother, do you?

602
00:29:49,809 --> 00:29:50,909
Just because I have the same name.

603
00:29:50,909 --> 00:29:51,942
Jin Woo!

604
00:29:51,942 --> 00:29:54,842
(Nice to meet you, Jin Woo.)

605
00:29:55,409 --> 00:29:57,342
- I got a message.
- What is this?

606
00:29:59,675 --> 00:30:02,775
(The first message is sent
to the older women and younger men.)

607
00:30:03,021 --> 00:30:04,289
The first message.

608
00:30:06,481 --> 00:30:07,347
What?

609
00:30:07,856 --> 00:30:08,823
Why? What is it?

610
00:30:09,592 --> 00:30:10,625
Right now?

611
00:30:11,292 --> 00:30:13,694
Right now? The names?

612
00:30:13,695 --> 00:30:17,097
(Please text the name of the person
who made the best first impression.)

613
00:30:17,098 --> 00:30:18,265
Right away?

614
00:30:18,333 --> 00:30:20,705
They have to make their choices
right away.

615
00:30:21,870 --> 00:30:23,504
It felt too sudden for me.

616
00:30:24,006 --> 00:30:25,406
I was a bit taken aback,

617
00:30:25,674 --> 00:30:28,046
but since I knew exactly who I liked,

618
00:30:28,110 --> 00:30:30,115
I sent the message without hesitation.

619
00:30:36,251 --> 00:30:41,722
(Whom did they choose
for their first impressions?)

620
00:30:41,723 --> 00:30:44,091
(Exploring Yeon House
after the first impression vote)

621
00:30:44,092 --> 00:30:46,665
- Shall we check out the rooms?
- Shall we take a look together?

622
00:30:48,163 --> 00:30:49,130
It's pretty.

623
00:30:49,431 --> 00:30:51,132
- Right?
- It's so pretty.

624
00:30:52,200 --> 00:30:53,872
What is this? Is it a heated pool?

625
00:30:54,236 --> 00:30:55,540
There's a heated pool too.

626
00:30:56,004 --> 00:30:58,872
The women's and men's quarters
are separate.

627
00:30:59,174 --> 00:31:01,041
Look, the names are written over there.

628
00:31:01,042 --> 00:31:03,444
(Nameplates)

629
00:31:03,445 --> 00:31:06,046
- Choi Yu Jin.
- Right.

630
00:31:06,381 --> 00:31:07,281
Great.

631
00:31:07,282 --> 00:31:08,782
It's us two together.

632
00:31:09,084 --> 00:31:10,384
I guess it's us two.

633
00:31:10,385 --> 00:31:11,252
(They'll be living together in pairs.)

634
00:31:11,387 --> 00:31:12,286
Great.

635
00:31:12,521 --> 00:31:13,755
(Looking around the rooms together)

636
00:31:13,756 --> 00:31:15,857
- How should we look around?
- Shall we take a look around?

637
00:31:15,858 --> 00:31:17,358
It's so cute.

638
00:31:17,359 --> 00:31:18,659
It's so pretty.

639
00:31:18,660 --> 00:31:20,895
It's so nice!

640
00:31:22,297 --> 00:31:24,331
It's a bedroom right away?

641
00:31:24,332 --> 00:31:27,235
(Yeon House stands out
with its clean interior design.)

642
00:31:27,236 --> 00:31:28,335
It's so pretty.

643
00:31:29,338 --> 00:31:31,472
- The room is so nice.
- I know, right?

644
00:31:31,773 --> 00:31:34,108
I wonder what the Talk Room is for.

645
00:31:34,409 --> 00:31:35,476
Shall we go and check out the Talk Room?

646
00:31:35,501 --> 00:31:37,907
- Who wants to go to the Talk Room?
- Shall we all go there and talk?

647
00:31:39,014 --> 00:31:40,047
(A special space next to the common area)

648
00:31:40,048 --> 00:31:41,048
There is a Talk Room.

649
00:31:41,049 --> 00:31:42,049
(The Talk Room)

650
00:31:42,417 --> 00:31:44,084
You need a passcode to enter.

651
00:31:44,085 --> 00:31:45,886
(It's a private space for two.)

652
00:31:45,887 --> 00:31:47,755
(Newly introduced in Season Two)

653
00:31:47,756 --> 00:31:49,823
This is a new space
introduced in Season Two.

654
00:31:49,824 --> 00:31:50,691
It's called the Talk Room.

655
00:31:51,426 --> 00:31:53,193
The choice belongs to you,

656
00:31:53,194 --> 00:31:54,395
so it doesn't bother me at all.

657
00:31:54,663 --> 00:31:57,498
I hope you won't get hurt.

658
00:31:58,234 --> 00:32:00,200
Hey, don't do that.

659
00:32:00,402 --> 00:32:02,536
I felt betrayed.

660
00:32:02,704 --> 00:32:04,238
This is what I think.

661
00:32:04,240 --> 00:32:06,741
After all, it's only our second day here.

662
00:32:09,211 --> 00:32:11,078
While I was there,
I kept thinking about you.

663
00:32:11,079 --> 00:32:12,647
I'm sure...

664
00:32:12,881 --> 00:32:14,715
things will definitely change
once we talk.

665
00:32:14,716 --> 00:32:16,283
What's that?

666
00:32:19,988 --> 00:32:21,221
We're talking.

667
00:32:26,094 --> 00:32:28,266
How can the atmosphere be this different?

668
00:32:28,730 --> 00:32:29,663
(Talk Room)

669
00:32:29,664 --> 00:32:33,033
(What kind of stories will unfold here
in the future?)

670
00:32:33,034 --> 00:32:34,635
Shall we go to our rooms
and unpack our bags?

671
00:32:34,636 --> 00:32:36,470
- Unpacking?
- Let's unpack.

672
00:32:36,471 --> 00:32:39,007
- Should we set a time to meet up again?
- Let's not do that.

673
00:32:39,008 --> 00:32:39,907
Great.

674
00:32:40,242 --> 00:32:41,676
- Don't do that.
- Let's take it easy.

675
00:32:42,344 --> 00:32:43,581
You can't come out tomorrow.

676
00:32:44,913 --> 00:32:46,347
- See you later.
- See you later.

677
00:32:46,348 --> 00:32:48,249
See you later.

678
00:32:48,250 --> 00:32:50,217
- See you later.
- All right.

679
00:32:50,218 --> 00:32:51,068
(Ji Hye and Ju Hee, Ji Seung and Yu Jin)

680
00:32:51,092 --> 00:32:51,919
(Si Won and Yun So, Jun Han and Jin Woo)

681
00:32:52,253 --> 00:32:54,454
I think I'm going to pass out tonight.

682
00:32:54,723 --> 00:32:57,462
- How many hours of sleep did you get?
- I only slept for two hours.

683
00:32:57,993 --> 00:32:58,960
That's similar to me.

684
00:32:58,961 --> 00:33:00,899
- Really?
- I slept for about that long as well.

685
00:33:01,331 --> 00:33:02,930
I was too nervous.

686
00:33:04,299 --> 00:33:07,301
Is there anyone among the men
who is your ideal type?

687
00:33:07,736 --> 00:33:09,036
Are you asking that already?

688
00:33:09,204 --> 00:33:11,605
In terms of looks,

689
00:33:11,606 --> 00:33:14,108
everyone is so handsome.

690
00:33:14,743 --> 00:33:16,777
Did you have someone in mind, Yu Jin?

691
00:33:16,878 --> 00:33:18,545
Well.

692
00:33:18,546 --> 00:33:19,980
- I'm not sure yet.
- Is that so?

693
00:33:19,981 --> 00:33:21,748
- Yes.
- She's keeping it a secret.

694
00:33:21,749 --> 00:33:24,384
I think both of them are
intentionally holding back.

695
00:33:25,687 --> 00:33:29,723
(Meanwhile, in Ji Hye and Ju Hee's room)

696
00:33:30,592 --> 00:33:32,293
- Is there anyone you like?
- Sorry?

697
00:33:32,294 --> 00:33:33,665
Is there anyone who caught your eye?

698
00:33:33,829 --> 00:33:35,596
I'm not sure yet.

699
00:33:35,831 --> 00:33:36,798
Really?

700
00:33:37,299 --> 00:33:38,370
Do you have someone in mind?

701
00:33:39,334 --> 00:33:41,869
I just chose the person who seemed
to have the best personality.

702
00:33:43,438 --> 00:33:45,406
I really have no idea.

703
00:33:45,774 --> 00:33:47,174
We should at least have a talk
or something.

704
00:33:47,175 --> 00:33:50,311
- We haven't had the chance to talk.
- Exactly.

705
00:33:50,712 --> 00:33:52,880
- Don't you think they seem quite young?
- Yes.

706
00:33:52,881 --> 00:33:54,048
All of them, right?

707
00:33:54,783 --> 00:33:56,350
I think they seem quite young.

708
00:33:57,185 --> 00:33:59,020
- All of them.
- I was actually quite surprised.

709
00:33:59,021 --> 00:34:01,192
The guys who sat over here and over there.

710
00:34:01,723 --> 00:34:03,390
I thought they were K-pop trainees.

711
00:34:03,859 --> 00:34:05,459
- They look so young.
- That's true.

712
00:34:05,794 --> 00:34:07,528
They really looked like idols.

713
00:34:07,529 --> 00:34:08,896
Right.

714
00:34:08,897 --> 00:34:11,132
I wonder if the guys are
also talking right now.

715
00:34:11,133 --> 00:34:13,300
- Asking each other who they voted for?
- Probably.

716
00:34:13,635 --> 00:34:14,635
Of course.

717
00:34:15,103 --> 00:34:18,072
(Yun So and Si Won's room)

718
00:34:18,240 --> 00:34:20,441
Si Won, may I ask who made
the best first impression on you?

719
00:34:22,077 --> 00:34:23,077
He's asking right away.

720
00:34:23,245 --> 00:34:25,450
- First impression?
- The person you just voted for earlier?

721
00:34:25,714 --> 00:34:27,048
For the text message,

722
00:34:27,783 --> 00:34:29,484
I chose Ji Seung.

723
00:34:29,485 --> 00:34:30,818
- Who?
- Ji Seung.

724
00:34:31,086 --> 00:34:32,153
Really?

725
00:34:32,754 --> 00:34:33,887
The person who sat next to me.

726
00:34:35,924 --> 00:34:40,194
I cast my first impression vote
for Ji Seung.

727
00:34:40,762 --> 00:34:42,896
The most memorable part was that...

728
00:34:42,897 --> 00:34:44,831
she spoke very enthusiastically,

729
00:34:44,832 --> 00:34:46,467
and when I saw her profile,

730
00:34:46,468 --> 00:34:48,602
she was exactly my type.

731
00:34:48,870 --> 00:34:52,039
I think her voice left
the strongest impression.

732
00:34:53,975 --> 00:34:54,908
Who did you choose?

733
00:34:55,377 --> 00:34:56,877
I chose Ju Hee.

734
00:34:56,878 --> 00:34:58,179
- Ju Hee?
- With short hair.

735
00:34:58,947 --> 00:35:00,180
Their choices didn't overlap.

736
00:35:00,748 --> 00:35:01,982
I chose Ju Hee.

737
00:35:01,983 --> 00:35:03,917
(Yun So's first impression vote
was Ju Hee.)

738
00:35:03,918 --> 00:35:06,020
Honestly, when I first saw Ju Hee,

739
00:35:07,522 --> 00:35:09,194
she seemed to have a great personality,

740
00:35:10,025 --> 00:35:12,560
and her looks were exactly my style,
so I liked her.

741
00:35:13,161 --> 00:35:16,230
(Si Won and Yun So's interests
didn't overlap.)

742
00:35:16,598 --> 00:35:19,600
(The men gathered in the common area
first after unpacking.)

743
00:35:19,601 --> 00:35:21,602
- Yun So, where was the meat?
- Here.

744
00:35:22,704 --> 00:35:24,405
The men arrived at the kitchen first.

745
00:35:25,141 --> 00:35:26,974
I noticed there were pork belly,
bacon, and ham...

746
00:35:27,375 --> 00:35:28,241
inside.

747
00:35:28,577 --> 00:35:31,946
(Just then, Ji Hye and Ju Hee
enter the common area.)

748
00:35:31,947 --> 00:35:33,114
- Hello.
- Hey.

749
00:35:33,115 --> 00:35:34,215
Hey.

750
00:35:34,216 --> 00:35:35,116
(Spotting Ju Hee)

751
00:35:35,117 --> 00:35:36,421
You're good at cooking Korean food.

752
00:35:36,685 --> 00:35:38,653
- You're good at cooking Korean food.
- Yes.

753
00:35:40,622 --> 00:35:43,724
From what I can see,
Yun So is definitely into Ju Hee.

754
00:35:44,492 --> 00:35:46,760
Do you prefer kimchi stew
or doenjang stew?

755
00:35:47,662 --> 00:35:49,129
- I prefer kimchi stew.
- Kimchi stew?

756
00:35:50,232 --> 00:35:52,500
But if we make kimchi stew,

757
00:35:52,734 --> 00:35:54,870
everyone might get chili powder
stuck in their teeth.

758
00:35:54,871 --> 00:35:56,136
That's charming, actually.

759
00:35:56,480 --> 00:35:58,805
- Shall we pick it out for each other?
- Sure. Let's do that.

760
00:36:00,208 --> 00:36:02,242
She's so cool.

761
00:36:02,243 --> 00:36:03,770
She says getting chili powder
stuck in your teeth...

762
00:36:03,794 --> 00:36:04,650
is charming and nice.

763
00:36:04,913 --> 00:36:06,680
- Well.
- It's all fine for her.

764
00:36:06,681 --> 00:36:07,615
She's chill.

765
00:36:07,616 --> 00:36:08,516
It's not a big deal.

766
00:36:08,517 --> 00:36:11,919
She's saying they have no time
to worry about things like that.

767
00:36:12,821 --> 00:36:15,556
(Ji Seung and Yu Jin are here too.)

768
00:36:15,790 --> 00:36:16,690
We're the last.

769
00:36:17,758 --> 00:36:18,759
Hello there.

770
00:36:18,760 --> 00:36:20,027
Hello.

771
00:36:20,028 --> 00:36:21,395
I'm barefoot too.

772
00:36:21,930 --> 00:36:24,798
- That's cute.
- So, it's stocked like this?

773
00:36:24,799 --> 00:36:26,504
We don't really make it from scratch?

774
00:36:27,836 --> 00:36:28,869
Is it pre-made?

775
00:36:29,571 --> 00:36:31,172
There's braised kimchi too.

776
00:36:31,573 --> 00:36:34,208
Then, let's make pork belly kimchi stew.

777
00:36:34,209 --> 00:36:35,175
Great.

778
00:36:35,176 --> 00:36:37,878
(The dinner menu was quickly decided
as soon as the ladies arrived.)

779
00:36:38,713 --> 00:36:40,180
You said you're good at cooking, Ju Hee.

780
00:36:40,181 --> 00:36:41,915
Yes. Should we take out the green onions?

781
00:36:41,916 --> 00:36:43,586
You should be the head chef today,
and I will be the sous chef.

782
00:36:43,587 --> 00:36:46,420
If you call us, we will take out
whatever you need.

783
00:36:47,088 --> 00:36:48,155
Do you need anything right now?

784
00:36:48,423 --> 00:36:49,423
Are you the main chef?

785
00:36:49,891 --> 00:36:52,559
- Main chef?
- But isn't everything already made?

786
00:36:52,560 --> 00:36:53,798
It's more like a pre-made meal kit.

787
00:36:54,262 --> 00:36:55,262
Because...

788
00:36:55,263 --> 00:36:56,363
(Disappointed)

789
00:36:56,465 --> 00:36:59,266
it'll take too long
if we cook it from scratch.

790
00:37:05,206 --> 00:37:06,139
Is it too bland?

791
00:37:06,574 --> 00:37:08,241
No, it's just too sweet.

792
00:37:08,242 --> 00:37:10,076
I think we should add something more.

793
00:37:10,077 --> 00:37:10,977
(Yun So is sticking around Ju Hee.)

794
00:37:10,978 --> 00:37:11,978
The broth.

795
00:37:13,114 --> 00:37:14,848
(Broth tablet)

796
00:37:14,849 --> 00:37:15,816
And...

797
00:37:17,252 --> 00:37:18,252
kimchi broth?

798
00:37:18,920 --> 00:37:21,922
(Stirring)

799
00:37:23,325 --> 00:37:25,426
The ingredients.

800
00:37:25,827 --> 00:37:26,693
It looks good.

801
00:37:26,694 --> 00:37:28,028
(They're having a great time together.)

802
00:37:28,029 --> 00:37:29,496
Yun So is good.

803
00:37:29,497 --> 00:37:31,498
- He's marking his territory.
- He's good.

804
00:37:31,666 --> 00:37:34,401
Yun So is like a reliable ox.

805
00:37:35,337 --> 00:37:37,537
He seems very steadfast and dependable.

806
00:37:38,873 --> 00:37:40,807
That works like magic.

807
00:37:40,808 --> 00:37:42,709
(The kitchen is filled
with their own special chemistry.)

808
00:37:42,710 --> 00:37:44,048
That must feel so good.

809
00:37:44,679 --> 00:37:45,946
We're done.

810
00:37:45,947 --> 00:37:49,449
(The two finished the kimchi stew
together.)

811
00:37:52,120 --> 00:37:55,089
(Jin Woo silently gathers
the tableware...)

812
00:37:55,090 --> 00:37:58,158
(and sets the table by himself.)

813
00:37:59,227 --> 00:38:01,995
(Wiping)

814
00:38:02,297 --> 00:38:03,230
(Doing the dishes too)

815
00:38:03,231 --> 00:38:04,932
He's quite attentive to details.

816
00:38:06,568 --> 00:38:08,369
I was going to do that.

817
00:38:08,370 --> 00:38:10,037
- These need to be washed, right?
- Yes.

818
00:38:10,038 --> 00:38:11,772
- I'll do it.
- You're so quick. Thank you.

819
00:38:11,773 --> 00:38:12,940
It's nothing.

820
00:38:15,010 --> 00:38:18,179
On top of his good looks,

821
00:38:18,180 --> 00:38:20,381
he even takes the initiative
to do the dishes.

822
00:38:20,382 --> 00:38:22,817
I can see a certain warmth in him.

823
00:38:22,818 --> 00:38:25,019
That was quite impressive.

824
00:38:26,054 --> 00:38:28,622
Ji Seung must have voted for Jin Woo.

825
00:38:28,623 --> 00:38:29,590
Ji Seung?

826
00:38:30,191 --> 00:38:33,160
(Did Ji Seung vote for Jin Woo?)

827
00:38:33,795 --> 00:38:35,763
- May I help you chop these together?
- Sure.

828
00:38:36,898 --> 00:38:40,067
I think this would taste delicious
with cream cheese.

829
00:38:40,068 --> 00:38:41,668
- The candied walnuts.
- Right?

830
00:38:41,669 --> 00:38:43,637
(Preparing desserts at the same time)

831
00:38:43,638 --> 00:38:45,543
What is this?
You can try one of the pieces that failed.

832
00:38:45,707 --> 00:38:46,907
Try this failed one.

833
00:38:46,908 --> 00:38:47,908
Oh, my.

834
00:38:48,610 --> 00:38:49,677
Try this failed one.

835
00:38:49,678 --> 00:38:50,878
(Feeding him)

836
00:38:50,879 --> 00:38:51,779
What?

837
00:38:53,048 --> 00:38:54,848
He didn't even take it with his hand.

838
00:38:54,849 --> 00:38:57,184
- That was smooth.
- He went straight for the bite.

839
00:38:57,819 --> 00:38:59,186
What should we do with him?

840
00:38:59,187 --> 00:39:00,958
He truly embodies
the charm of a younger guy.

841
00:39:02,657 --> 00:39:03,957
Try this failed one.

842
00:39:06,094 --> 00:39:08,429
(Si Won voted for Ji Seung.)

843
00:39:08,430 --> 00:39:09,563
Yes, that's right.

844
00:39:09,931 --> 00:39:11,331
You can just eat it straight.

845
00:39:12,200 --> 00:39:14,201
(Jin Woo picks up a strawberry...)

846
00:39:14,903 --> 00:39:17,471
(and heads somewhere.)

847
00:39:17,472 --> 00:39:18,405
Have a strawberry.

848
00:39:18,406 --> 00:39:19,406
Thank you.

849
00:39:20,208 --> 00:39:22,009
- Have a strawberry.
- Thank you.

850
00:39:22,010 --> 00:39:23,043
Would you like some more?

851
00:39:26,481 --> 00:39:27,481
Oh, my.

852
00:39:32,821 --> 00:39:35,756
During the dinner preparations,
it seemed like...

853
00:39:35,757 --> 00:39:38,893
Jin Woo is showing some interest
in Ji Hye.

854
00:39:38,894 --> 00:39:40,080
(Did Jin Woo vote for Ji Hye?)

855
00:39:40,105 --> 00:39:41,432
Would you like some alcohol?

856
00:39:41,803 --> 00:39:43,007
- Wine, please.
- Wine?

857
00:39:43,918 --> 00:39:45,610
- Cheers.
- It's a small crowd.

858
00:39:45,611 --> 00:39:48,713
(The first dinner at Yeon House
with everyone together)

859
00:39:50,404 --> 00:39:51,883
That must be so good.

860
00:39:52,751 --> 00:39:54,119
It's delicious.

861
00:39:57,183 --> 00:39:58,423
How much can you all drink?

862
00:40:00,465 --> 00:40:02,269
I can drink about three bottles.

863
00:40:02,375 --> 00:40:03,949
- Three bottles of soju?
- Impressive.

864
00:40:03,974 --> 00:40:06,458
- That's a lot.
- Which means he can actually drink four.

865
00:40:06,839 --> 00:40:07,559
Right.

866
00:40:08,693 --> 00:40:10,094
Here he goes again.

867
00:40:10,300 --> 00:40:13,537
He'd probably throw up
and cry after one bottle.

868
00:40:13,633 --> 00:40:15,087
You'd have to put him in a taxi
and send him home.

869
00:40:15,111 --> 00:40:17,248
- You're talking about yourself.
- That's adorable.

870
00:40:17,348 --> 00:40:19,295
You sound very confident.

871
00:40:19,319 --> 00:40:22,379
I can drink that much,
but I don't really drink often.

872
00:40:22,814 --> 00:40:24,408
I see. So you don't drink much.

873
00:40:24,821 --> 00:40:25,955
Are you a drinker?

874
00:40:26,349 --> 00:40:29,118
Me? No. Maybe once a month?

875
00:40:29,479 --> 00:40:30,682
- Since you work out, right?
- Yes.

876
00:40:30,706 --> 00:40:32,679
If it's once a month,
you're basically not a drinker.

877
00:40:33,539 --> 00:40:37,192
- How often do you drink?
- I'm not much of a drinker either.

878
00:40:37,332 --> 00:40:39,156
I can drink maybe half a bottle
to one bottle of wine.

879
00:40:41,118 --> 00:40:42,458
I like wine too.

880
00:40:42,571 --> 00:40:44,568
- Really? Do you prefer white wine?
- Yes.

881
00:40:44,623 --> 00:40:46,506
- You drank white wine earlier.
- I'm not picky about the type.

882
00:40:46,531 --> 00:40:47,488
Really?

883
00:40:47,500 --> 00:40:49,005
I like wine too.

884
00:40:49,733 --> 00:40:52,776
- Si Won is really handsome.
- He really is. I told you.

885
00:40:52,801 --> 00:40:55,144
I think I also drink
once or twice a month.

886
00:40:56,012 --> 00:40:58,301
So none of them are really drinkers.

887
00:40:58,325 --> 00:40:59,877
I don't go out of my way to drink.

888
00:41:00,004 --> 00:41:02,446
Hangovers got worse as I got older.

889
00:41:03,091 --> 00:41:04,548
- As you got older?
- Older?

890
00:41:08,237 --> 00:41:09,620
You're not serious, are you?

891
00:41:09,986 --> 00:41:10,821
That's hilarious.

892
00:41:10,975 --> 00:41:13,219
Am I not allowed to mention age?

893
00:41:13,243 --> 00:41:14,025
Of course not.

894
00:41:15,265 --> 00:41:17,033
(Giggling)

895
00:41:18,248 --> 00:41:20,815
- I'm already tipsy. It's been a while.
- A message just came in.

896
00:41:21,841 --> 00:41:23,968
- I got a message.
- Should we read it together?

897
00:41:27,224 --> 00:41:28,857
Wait. They got a message.

898
00:41:33,362 --> 00:41:34,262
Am I reading this right?

899
00:41:34,286 --> 00:41:35,985
- What's going on?
- What does that mean?

900
00:41:36,381 --> 00:41:39,156
I was honestly shocked
when I got the message.

901
00:41:39,289 --> 00:41:40,518
What is it?

902
00:41:41,539 --> 00:41:42,793
They all look shocked.

903
00:41:45,601 --> 00:41:48,793
I didn't expect them
to reveal it publicly like this.

904
00:41:50,560 --> 00:41:53,270
The mood suddenly turned awkward.

905
00:41:57,974 --> 00:42:00,492
(The people who received zero votes
on the first-impression vote...)

906
00:42:00,517 --> 00:42:01,639
(are Yoo Jin Woo and Park Ji Hye.)

907
00:42:01,692 --> 00:42:03,372
They're announcing it like that?

908
00:42:06,616 --> 00:42:09,869
They literally revealed
who got zero votes by text!

909
00:42:09,893 --> 00:42:10,849
Really?

910
00:42:11,681 --> 00:42:13,451
How are they supposed to recover
from this atmosphere?

911
00:42:13,476 --> 00:42:14,496
Tell me about it.

912
00:42:14,861 --> 00:42:20,063
(The ones who received zero votes
are revealed to everyone.)

913
00:42:20,773 --> 00:42:22,238
Oh, no. They got zero votes.

914
00:42:22,262 --> 00:42:24,228
I suddenly started feeling tipsy.

915
00:42:25,326 --> 00:42:26,997
It still didn't feel real, though.

916
00:42:30,552 --> 00:42:35,773
Seriously, I couldn't believe it.
I read it like five times.

917
00:42:38,277 --> 00:42:41,151
It said nobody chose me
in the first-impression vote.

918
00:42:42,337 --> 00:42:44,515
Look at her expression. It feels so real.

919
00:42:44,582 --> 00:42:46,050
Why did nobody choose me?

920
00:42:48,009 --> 00:42:49,787
Could this really happen to me?

921
00:42:50,361 --> 00:42:52,095
That's brutal.

922
00:42:52,195 --> 00:42:54,264
What am I supposed to do now?

923
00:42:54,606 --> 00:42:57,300
I wanted to go home.

924
00:42:57,927 --> 00:42:58,968
This is harsh.

925
00:42:59,041 --> 00:43:00,307
(Another message is delivered.)

926
00:43:00,308 --> 00:43:01,308
What now?

927
00:43:03,953 --> 00:43:07,652
When I received the second message,
I was shocked again.

928
00:43:09,552 --> 00:43:10,552
What did it say?

929
00:43:10,553 --> 00:43:12,382
(After the zero-vote announcement,)

930
00:43:12,816 --> 00:43:15,003
(Jin Woo and Ji Hye are given
a chance to talk...)

931
00:43:15,028 --> 00:43:16,981
(1-on-1 for 30 minutes
with the person they like.)

932
00:43:17,036 --> 00:43:18,916
They're immediately giving them a benefit.

933
00:43:19,807 --> 00:43:21,702
It says to choose the person you like
right now.

934
00:43:21,703 --> 00:43:24,260
(But only the first person to act
can take the opportunity.)

935
00:43:25,024 --> 00:43:26,824
That totally caught me off guard.

936
00:43:27,319 --> 00:43:28,058
All of a sudden?

937
00:43:28,709 --> 00:43:31,192
The first-impression vote happened...

938
00:43:31,770 --> 00:43:35,566
literally ten minutes after we all met.

939
00:43:35,770 --> 00:43:38,902
So getting zero votes didn't really
mean that much to me.

940
00:43:39,116 --> 00:43:43,146
I just focused on who I wanted to talk to.

941
00:43:43,702 --> 00:43:45,409
Exactly. It's not that big of a deal.

942
00:43:46,522 --> 00:43:48,546
This could actually become an opportunity.

943
00:43:48,798 --> 00:43:51,988
(Who will grab this first-come,
first-served opportunity?)

944
00:43:53,106 --> 00:43:54,351
This is so interesting.

945
00:43:58,782 --> 00:44:00,291
Go now! Move.

946
00:44:01,004 --> 00:44:02,060
Now!

947
00:44:06,376 --> 00:44:10,740
Ju Hee, would you like to come
to the Talk Room with me?

948
00:44:11,021 --> 00:44:12,169
- Me? Yes.
- Yes.

949
00:44:13,248 --> 00:44:14,427
(Jin Woo moves quickly
and takes the opportunity.)

950
00:44:14,428 --> 00:44:16,646
That was actually really brave of him.

951
00:44:16,647 --> 00:44:17,580
(And Ji Hye misses her chance.)

952
00:44:17,581 --> 00:44:22,552
I was too nervous,
so I couldn't ask anyone.

953
00:44:25,333 --> 00:44:28,339
For older women, it's even harder...

954
00:44:28,585 --> 00:44:30,308
to make the first move
in a situation like that.

955
00:44:30,333 --> 00:44:33,056
Because this probably feels
very significant to them.

956
00:44:33,170 --> 00:44:35,498
If I were there and got zero votes,

957
00:44:35,824 --> 00:44:37,976
- there's nothing you can do about it.
- That's true.

958
00:44:37,976 --> 00:44:41,563
I'd say, "If the vote happened right now,
the results would be very different."

959
00:44:41,605 --> 00:44:43,934
And then I'd stare right into the eyes
of the person I liked.

960
00:44:43,959 --> 00:44:45,861
That's such a good move.
That's really attractive.

961
00:44:46,493 --> 00:44:48,780
- You can grab your coat.
- Okay. I'll get mine.

962
00:44:48,781 --> 00:44:49,613
(Moving to the Talk Room)

963
00:44:52,878 --> 00:44:54,684
Yun So looks upset.

964
00:44:59,889 --> 00:45:02,225
(Peeking)

965
00:45:05,050 --> 00:45:06,257
Yun So looks uneasy.

966
00:45:07,503 --> 00:45:11,501
I didn't expect Jin Woo to ask Ju Hee out.

967
00:45:12,342 --> 00:45:14,704
Earlier, we guys talked among ourselves.

968
00:45:14,835 --> 00:45:20,410
He said he was kind of interested
in Yu Jin.

969
00:45:22,154 --> 00:45:23,154
Then why?

970
00:45:23,934 --> 00:45:26,316
(Did Jin Woo choose Yu Jin
in the first-impression vote?)

971
00:45:26,652 --> 00:45:29,325
Did you guys tell each other
who you voted for earlier?

972
00:45:29,350 --> 00:45:31,201
- Yes, we did.
- All of us.

973
00:45:31,225 --> 00:45:33,250
- Really?
- You shared that?

974
00:45:33,485 --> 00:45:35,892
- I voted for Ju Hee.
- Ju Hee? I chose Ji Seung.

975
00:45:36,864 --> 00:45:38,457
I chose Yu Jin.

976
00:45:38,481 --> 00:45:39,796
I heard.

977
00:45:39,863 --> 00:45:42,065
(Jin Woo chose Yu Jin
in the first-impression vote.)

978
00:45:42,163 --> 00:45:45,435
Yu Jin sat right across from me.

979
00:45:45,656 --> 00:45:49,416
As we talked, I kept noticing her
without even realizing it.

980
00:45:49,995 --> 00:45:52,175
We also made eye contact many times.

981
00:45:53,001 --> 00:45:55,873
(While introducing themselves,)

982
00:45:55,965 --> 00:45:57,696
My brother has the same name.

983
00:45:57,720 --> 00:45:58,709
It's an honor.

984
00:46:00,520 --> 00:46:04,487
My strongest first impression of her
was that she seemed very kind.

985
00:46:06,489 --> 00:46:08,232
(But afterward,)

986
00:46:08,256 --> 00:46:12,395
(Jin Woo subtly took care of Ji Hye.)

987
00:46:13,296 --> 00:46:16,501
(And why has he invited Ju Hee
to the Talk Room?)

988
00:46:16,502 --> 00:46:17,502
Honestly,

989
00:46:17,955 --> 00:46:22,580
Ju Hee was the person
I'd talked to the least.

990
00:46:23,461 --> 00:46:27,120
So I became curious
about what she was thinking,

991
00:46:27,144 --> 00:46:28,419
and I invited her.

992
00:46:28,420 --> 00:46:29,980
(He became curious about Ju Hee
because they hadn't talked much.)

993
00:46:30,146 --> 00:46:32,648
Jin Woo said he wanted
to get to know everyone.

994
00:46:33,046 --> 00:46:35,212
He's more cautious than I expected.

995
00:46:36,392 --> 00:46:39,122
(After Jin Woo and Ju Hee left)

996
00:46:39,491 --> 00:46:42,286
It suddenly feels so quiet now
that two people are absent.

997
00:46:43,151 --> 00:46:45,297
- The mood got awkward.
- Really awkward.

998
00:46:45,298 --> 00:46:48,798
- I'm so curious.
- I want to sneak into the Talk Room too.

999
00:46:50,236 --> 00:46:51,762
What are they even talking about in there?

1000
00:46:54,957 --> 00:46:57,901
Did you ladies share
who you voted for afterward?

1001
00:46:58,362 --> 00:47:01,521
- Share? No.
- The person you voted for.

1002
00:47:01,660 --> 00:47:02,627
Did you guys share?

1003
00:47:02,651 --> 00:47:04,260
- Yeah, we all talked about it.
- Seriously?

1004
00:47:04,261 --> 00:47:05,540
- Yes.
- You can do that?

1005
00:47:05,564 --> 00:47:06,777
You all know already?

1006
00:47:06,894 --> 00:47:09,419
- We do, yes.
- Really?

1007
00:47:09,607 --> 00:47:11,815
Are we allowed to share that information?

1008
00:47:12,142 --> 00:47:13,712
- They're so different.
- I'm so curious.

1009
00:47:13,751 --> 00:47:15,115
The women didn't share anything.

1010
00:47:15,140 --> 00:47:16,140
Is that so?

1011
00:47:16,626 --> 00:47:17,626
Really?

1012
00:47:17,627 --> 00:47:20,497
(Si Won chose Ji Seung
in the first-impression vote.)

1013
00:47:20,958 --> 00:47:24,454
(Who did Ji Seung vote for?)

1014
00:47:24,455 --> 00:47:25,534
I think she chose Jin Woo.

1015
00:47:27,170 --> 00:47:30,440
I picked Si Won
as my favorite first impression.

1016
00:47:30,540 --> 00:47:31,579
Really?

1017
00:47:31,603 --> 00:47:33,938
He seems so decent.

1018
00:47:35,599 --> 00:47:37,141
And I really like his clear eyes.

1019
00:47:37,646 --> 00:47:39,344
He has beautiful eyes.

1020
00:47:39,765 --> 00:47:41,818
That's why I chose him.

1021
00:47:43,665 --> 00:47:45,445
(Ji Seung and Si Won chose each other.)

1022
00:47:45,446 --> 00:47:47,645
- That's nice.
- Amazing.

1023
00:47:48,391 --> 00:47:52,795
(Who did Ji Hye, who received zero votes,
choose?)

1024
00:47:52,848 --> 00:47:55,465
I like masculine men.

1025
00:47:56,360 --> 00:47:59,235
Single eyelids and a personality
that feels approachable.

1026
00:47:59,415 --> 00:48:01,720
I thought he might actually be cute.

1027
00:48:01,744 --> 00:48:02,481
Then it must be Jun Han.

1028
00:48:02,506 --> 00:48:04,740
(Did she choose the bubbly Jun Han?)

1029
00:48:05,198 --> 00:48:06,198
I'm curious.

1030
00:48:06,199 --> 00:48:08,144
(Or the masculine Yun So?)

1031
00:48:09,379 --> 00:48:11,181
- I chose Jun Han.
- I told you.

1032
00:48:11,301 --> 00:48:13,650
He seems like such a nice guy.

1033
00:48:13,682 --> 00:48:16,686
The moment he walked in,
he started smiling.

1034
00:48:16,853 --> 00:48:18,213
- Hello.
- Hi.

1035
00:48:19,289 --> 00:48:21,753
(Jun Han caught Ji Hye's attention.)

1036
00:48:21,778 --> 00:48:23,153
I'm so shy.

1037
00:48:25,028 --> 00:48:27,958
I was curious about him
because he seemed fun to talk to.

1038
00:48:30,808 --> 00:48:32,478
Ji Hye chose Jun Han
as her favorite first impression.

1039
00:48:32,503 --> 00:48:34,137
(Ji Hye liked Jun Han at first sight.)

1040
00:48:34,162 --> 00:48:35,596
- Can you do that?
- I know.

